  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      lymphorrehea remains the most frequent complication after axillary lymphadenectomy. we
      hyphothesize that the use of a bipolar vessel sealing may reduce the rate of lymph collection
      compared to the traditional surgical technique
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
